               <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>Σώπολις Φαλάκ<supplied reason="lost">ρου</supplied> <supplied reason="lost">τ</supplied>ὰν αὐτοῦτα ματέρα
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>αν Φαλ<supplied reason="lost">ακρ</supplied>ίαν εὐνοίας ἕνεκα
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text of Ampolo and Erdas 2019</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Sopolis son of Phalakros (honours/dedicates) his mother [---]a Phalakria, on account of her goodwill.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" source="http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/3PK3JKXR">
                <p>Sopolis figlio di Phalakros (ha onorato/eretto la statua di) sua madre [---] Phalakria per la sua benvolenza[trans. Ampolo and Erdas]</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--erected by Sopolis, son of Phalakros to his own mother, Phalakria, out of eunoia. IG 14.288 and other early eds thought this and IGLPa 46 were a single constr. M-P notes the differences. cf. Nenci ASNP 21 (1991), 920-9 for relevant discussion.--></p>
            </div>
